ffer within a limited time frame in order to give you enough time to make an informed and thoughtful decision we require employers to follow these guidelines fall winter and spring quarter 3 weeks minimum response time from receipt of the written offer summer quarter if you are offered full time employment at the end of a summer internship the decision deadline is november 30th this allows students to participate in the fall recruiting process non discrimination policy students are protected from discrimination on the basis of national origin race religion sex sexual orientation age disability or any other basis prohibited by applicable law employer presentations information sessions up groups career development center printer friendly version calendar schedule an appointment graphic calendar pages schedule an appointment with a career counselor quick links calendar career fair schedule career planning handbook career library vault guided career path facebook linkedin what is the cdc copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
